<doc id="589400" wikidata="Q7995148" url="?curid=589400" title="White Oak Pocosin">
<text>The White Oak Pocosin is a large swamp in northern Onslow County and southern Jones County, North Carolina in the United States. It provides the headwaters of the White Oak River. The word pocosin is a Native American word meaning &quot;swamp&quot;.</text><links>
